HEAPS
Heap data structure will store the data in arrays. It will be stored by trees and the values will be arranged by trees.
With the help of complete binary tree, the elements will be arranged acc.
With the help of priority queues, heaps got created.
As the data is stored in arrays, u can access the data by index values.
As trees got involved, definitely heaps come under non linear data structure.
It should follow complete binary tree

Types:
1) Bottom to Top approach
2) Top to Bottom approach

